<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-17T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-17T17:00:00-05:00" n="101" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.51/817a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-17T17:00:00-05:00">November 17, 1933—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>98. <hi rend="italic">New York Times</hi> publishes cable from Rio de
                            Janeiro dated November 16 that Finance Minister “in a departmental
                            report today” proposes a scheme for servicing Brazil’s foreign debts. Is
                            this a new move on the part of the Finance Minister?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>